			g(x)=2f(x+2)+(x+1)(x+3)=2f(x+2)+(x+2)^2-1.
			\end{align*}
			Ta có $g'(x)=2f'(x+2)-2(x+2)$. Suy ra
			\begin{align*}
			g'(x)=0\Leftrightarrow f'(x+2)=(x+2)\Leftrightarrow \left[\begin{aligned}& x+2=-1 \\ & x+2=0\\& x+2=1\\& x+2=2\end{aligned}\right.\Leftrightarrow \left[\begin{aligned}& x=-3 \\ & x=-2\\& x=-1\\ & x=0.\end{aligned}\right.
			\end{align*}
			Với $x=-2$ ta có $g(-2)=2f(0)+0^2-1=2\cdot \dfrac{1}{2}-1=0$.$\\$
